50x550.jpg 550w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink-156x156.jpg 156w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink-288x288.jpg 288w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink-500x500.jpg 500w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"h-ingredients\"\u003eIngredients \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLight Rum\u003c/strong\u003e – Choose a quality light rum.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDark Rum\u003c/strong\u003e – Choose a quality dark rum.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLime Juice\u003c/strong\u003e – Fresh squeezed lime juice is a must for this recipe.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrange Juice\u003c/strong\u003e – Fresh squeezed is best, bottled works in a pinch.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePassion Fruit Pureé\u003c/strong\u003e – Choose a \u003ca href=\"https://amzn.to/4gHPvg5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"\u003epassion fruit puree\u003c/a\u003e and if you can’t locate that you may also use passion fruit juice or passion fruit syrup in this recipe.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGrenadine\u003c/strong\u003e – \u003ca href=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/quick-easy-homemade-grenadine-syrup-only-3-ingredients/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003eMake your own grenadine\u003c/a\u003e or choose a store-bought option.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSimple Syrup\u003c/strong\u003e – This ingredient is optional (I find it to be more than sweet enough without it).\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGarnish Ideas\u003c/strong\u003e – Orange wheel or half-wheel orange slices, preserved cherry or maraschino cherry and a \u003ca href=\"https://amzn.to/4h274XH\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"\u003epaper umbrella\u003c/a\u003e never hurts.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe best glassware option for a hurricane is obviously a \u003ca href=\"https://amzn.to/3C066ww\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"\u003ehurricane glass\u003c/a\u003e. I use these glasses often for all sorts of tropical drinks. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"h-hurricane-drink-history\"\u003eHurricane Drink History \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Hurricane was invented in the early 1940s by Pat O’Brien’s in New Orleans. It was created as a response to a surplus of rum, which was easier to acquire than other liquors at that time. This popular drink helped bartenders move plenty of rum and it remains one of the most popular New Orleans cocktails to this day.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"960\" data-pin-url=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/hurricane-drink/?tp_image_id=136424\" data-pin-title=\"Hurricane Drink Recipe\" src=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink-.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink-.jpg 1200w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink--300x240.jpg 300w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink--1024x819.jpg 1024w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink--768x614.jpg 768w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink--100x80.jpg 100w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink--75x60.jpg 75w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink--750x600.jpg 750w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink--730x584.jpg 730w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Hurricane-Drink--700x560.jpg 700w, https://abeautifulmess.com/